def: A combining form signifying relating to the forehead or thefrontal bone; as, fronto-parietal, relating to the frontal and theparietal bones; fronto-nasal, etc.
To make or become white, or candied. [R.]
Made of silk; having a silky or flaxlike appearance. Coles.
One who, or that which, heightens.
Having the surface covered with irregular, impressed lines.
A confectioner. [Obs.]He will take your daughters to be confectionaries, and to be cooks. 1Sam. viii. 13.
A substance isomeric with, and resembling, indigo blue, andaccompanying it as a side product, in its artificial production.
Of or pertaining to an arc. Arcual measure of an angle (Math.),that in which the unit angle has its measuring arc equal to theradius of the circle.
Having a leaflike membrane on the nose; -- said of certainbats, esp. of the genera Phyllostoma and Rhinonycteris. See Vampire.
